  "text": "We adopt an automatic procedure to estimate speckle standard deviation from SAR images as in Frulla et al [CITATION_1] , which observed that the CV should be equal to the theoretical speckle standard deviation according to the number of looks of the SAR image for fully developed speckled images. However, the coefficient of variation measured over homogeneous regions on the images may differ from theoretical values due to several reasons such as the inherent image variations and the size of the selected sample.",
